<DOC><DOCNO> AP900808-0012 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-08-90 0144EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Iraq-BBC     08-08 0173</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Iraq-BBC,0178</SECOND><HEAD>Iraq Steps Up Efforts To Jam BBC World Service</HEAD><HEAD>With PM-Iraq-Kuwait Rdp, Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Iraq has stepped up its efforts to jam theArabic-language broadcasts of the British Broadcasting Corp. WorldService, the BBC said.   The BBC expanded its Arabic-language broadcasts from nine to 10{hours a day last week following the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait.   BBC engineers have detected interference with the WorldService's Arabic transmissions on a range of short-wave frequenciesserving the Middle East.   They have traced the jamming to a site south of Baghdad, the BBCsaid Tuesday. English-language broadcasts have not been affected.   ``Jamming the BBC is always the last resort of those who wish tosuppress the truth _ and in a way it is a tribute to the role ofthe World Service at times of crisis,'' said David Witherow, deputymanaging director of the BBC World Service.   ``Jamming is never entirely effective and I am sure thatlisteners throughout the region are relying on the BBC for news,''he said.</TEXT></DOC>